{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17477159","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17477159"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T22:58:14+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T22:58:14+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14221"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14221","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14221"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.03,0.06,0.02,0.03,0.86]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6908"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"53331"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"6908","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6908"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14221"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"38780"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"9"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"99"},{"type":"tags","id":"1804"},{"type":"tags","id":"1875"},{"type":"tags","id":"2602"},{"type":"tags","id":"4953"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4991"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"5351"},{"type":"tags","id":"11622"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"},{"type":"tags","id":"12732"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"15826"},{"type":"contributions","id":"32916"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44204"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45021"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"53331","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/53331"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 10-year-old Indigenous Australian girl presents to the General Practice clinic with her parent for a routine check-up. She has a history of acute rheumatic fever two years ago and has been on prophylactic treatment since then. She has no current symptoms and takes no other regular medications. Her immunisations are up to date. On examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. Cardiovascular examination reveals a soft systolic murmur at the apex.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHer most recent echocardiogram, performed six months ago, showed mild mitral regurgitation. Blood tests reveal a normal full blood count and C-reactive protein.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate management plan?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Switch to oral penicillin","Increase frequency of echocardiograms to monthly","Commence oral prednisolone","Cease prophylactic treatment","Continue current prophylaxis and annual echocardiograms"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis case highlights the management of rheumatic heart disease (RHD) in an Indigenous Australian child. RHD is significantly more prevalent in Indigenous populations compared to non-Indigenous Australians, making it a crucial health issue to address.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EContinue current prophylaxis and annual echocardiograms\u003C/strong\u003E is the most appropriate management plan. For children with a history of acute rheumatic fever and evidence of RHD, long-term prophylaxis is essential to prevent recurrence of rheumatic fever and progression of valve damage. The current standard of care is intramuscular benzathine penicillin G every 28 days, which should be continued. Annual echocardiograms are recommended to monitor valve function and disease progression.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECeasing prophylactic treatment\u003C/strong\u003E would be inappropriate and potentially dangerous. Even though the patient is currently asymptomatic, she remains at high risk for recurrent rheumatic fever, which could worsen her cardiac status.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESwitching to oral penicillin\u003C/strong\u003E is not recommended. Intramuscular benzathine penicillin G is preferred due to its long-acting nature and better adherence compared to daily oral antibiotics.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreasing frequency of echocardiograms to monthly\u003C/strong\u003E is unnecessary in a stable patient. Annual echocardiograms are sufficient for monitoring unless there are new symptoms or signs of worsening disease.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECommencing oral prednisolone\u003C/strong\u003E is not indicated. Corticosteroids are used in the acute phase of rheumatic fever to manage inflammation, not for long-term management of RHD.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe management of RHD in Indigenous Australian children requires a comprehensive approach, including education, regular follow-ups, and culturally appropriate care. It\u0027s crucial to ensure adherence to prophylaxis and regular monitoring to prevent disease progression and improve long-term outcomes.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Indigenous Australian children have higher rates of rheumatic heart disease compared to non-Indigenous children.","Benzathine penicillin G is the recommended prophylaxis for rheumatic heart disease in children.","Regular echocardiograms are essential for monitoring valve function in children with rheumatic heart disease."],"references":["Rwebembera, J., Marangou, J., Mwita, J.C. et al. 2023 World Heart Federation guidelines for the echocardiographic diagnosis of rheumatic heart disease. Nat Rev Cardiol 21, 250\u2013263 (2024). https://doi.org/10.1038/s41569-023-00940-9","RHD Australia (ARF/RHD writing group), National Heart Foundation of Australia and the Cardiac Society of Australia and New Zealand. Australian guidelines for prevention, diagnosis and management of acute rheumatic fever and rheumatic heart disease. 3rd ed. Darwin: RHD Australia, Menzies School of Health Research; 2020. Available from: https://www.rhdaustralia.org.au/arf-rhd-guidelines."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"38780"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14221"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"38780","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/38780"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-09-19T19:40:33+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-04-01T14:48:59+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6908"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"53331"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"2","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/2"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"9","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/9"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc76","name":"Paediatrics","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-01-16T08:39:03+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/72"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","nam